review_text: I think the training is amazing. I've been doing the other training from Ed. If this training could include a fictitious scenario to fill out the Google Sheet provided, it would be amazing, so you can have a better idea of what to add to them.
Ed is both super-knowledgeable and super-engaging and has clearly put a lot of thought into structuring this very insightful course.

Enjoyed this course as I have all Ed's other courses. Some very good insights that I, despite being familiar with the topics, gleaned from the course. Definitely take this course if you want to your AI projects to succeed.

Excellent starter and overview in either you are starting a role within organization for Ai adoption, or that you are starting a Ai startup company that is looking to build an Ai product, or better even an agency that is looking to provide Ai consulting services / software developments.
This is giving me a lot of good insight and will definitely help me with the other course that I'm currently taking that was also provided by Ed Donner.

Really enjoyed this course! Ed Donner explains AI strategy in a super clear way and shares practical frameworks and tools that make it easy to see how to kick off an AI initiative in any organisation. Very insightful and easy to follow. Definitely recommend!

'Ed..It was great to connect you on LinkedIn. I am in the last lecture of last module and can't stop myself to rate the quality, content and specially about you, your communication and way of explaining the things. Absolutely brilliant. I never imagine, someone can explain AI in such a simple way also. This is new and emerging field and as your said lot uncertainty and unpredictability, so it requires lot of courage to come and speak on such topics end to end is something amazing. Many congratulations to you for coming up such a great topic and course.'
This is very informative and touched down all aspects of Generative AI and quite informative,
I enjoyed this course. The instructor is upbeat, obviously knowledgeable from firsthand experience, does not talk down to students, and truly seems to care whether or not we're learning.
This is my third course from Ed Donner. He has again done excellent job in delivering the contents with right pace and visuals. He knows how to make a complex topic in crisp clear manner.

Very good course. Designed by an AI executive for business leaders, in business leader language. Very useful for designing AI strategies and initiatives in the company. Ed has excellent teaching methods for explaining complex concepts. His experience is invaluable. I'm very happy to have taken his course.

The Generative AI 2025 Executive Briefing is super helpful because it doesn't just teach you about the technology; it's designed to fundamentally reframe your mindset as a leader to drive strategic, impactful change with AI.
This course gives a fantastic roadmap to drive an AI project. All nuances are nicely covered!

One of the best courses I have taken. This is not a superficial course, Ed has put in enough details that will allow anybody in a position of making technology decisions to talk confidently about adopting Generative AI in their respective organizations.

Easy to follow and no nonsense guide. Good for leaders who want to get a start and understand all the jargons of AI and enables them to take decisions on AI projects. If you are a leader pitching in the business case, it guides you to prepare a successful one with frameworks and steps. I thoroughly enjoyed this. Thank you
Excellent course, very thorough but easy to follow introduction to AI. After listening to this I feel better able to communicate with the tech people.

The instructor, Ed, has a wealth of insights on AI. He clearly demonstrates his experience and expertise in this course. If you're working on AI, this is a great course to understand the bigger picture and impact to stakeholders and the business.
Ed's enthusiasm for the topic itself makes the course more interesting than it already is. Concepts are explained clearly and simply and his toolkits/frameworks are well thought out.
1) Overall well structured and touch-based on every aspect required to be known by AI leader.

Ed speaks lucidly about the landscape of AI for businesses, and I found the discussion on the technologies very enlightening. Thanks for making this, it's a brilliant strategic resource, really captures so much of what makes AI a black box to outsiders, and reveals what is going on with clarity. I especially found the explanation of the "magic" behind Agent AI's useful in this regard.

Solid executive-level overview that cuts through the Gen AI hype. Really appreciated the practical frameworks for AI decision-making and the focus on real business implementation. The RAG and agents sections were particularly relevant for enterprise use. Could use more expanded examples of successful transformations, but overall exactly what leaders need to understand the strategic side of Gen AI.

Ed's presentation style is fantastic. The way he gives you the expectation of what you'll be learning and then diving a bit more into the details is great. I learned a lot in a fairly short time. Definitely time well spent.
Straight to the Point and Executive-Ready

A great introduction to many new concepts with thoughtful discussion around challenges, risks, and buy-in for GenAI adoption. The course shared plenty of useful resources, and Ed Donner did a fantastic job keeping it engaging and focused. Highly recommended!

Ed did it again! This is the second course I’ve taken from Ed, and I really enjoyed it. It’s one of the most practical AI courses out there — no technical deep dives, just clear, real-world frameworks for AI strategy, decision-making, and leadership that I can apply right away at work.

Great framing. I personally benefitted from the tech overview (RAG, fine-tuning section) - would love to see more and will try his other classes. POV on vibe coding would be interesting as some companies are investing there. Loved the "date for the date" and acknowledgement uncertainty in R&D - reminded me of early days in enterprise data science. I was already familiar with business cases, change management, etc. . . - frameworks seemed very clear and simple and a good refresh.

Just wrapped up the course and and WOW, what a strategic game-changer! The course dives deep into enterprise‑level AI roadmapping, showcases real-world risk frameworks (with no fluff!), and provides tactical mitigation strategies that immediately sharpen decision-making
Very interactive and well presented for the context, full of great content and insights

I really enjoyed this course. Ed’s perspective on the latest in AI - and what executives need to understand and focus on - was incredibly valuable. It was also a great way to consolidate some of my existing AI knowledge.
Lots of very practical and applicable information in a little more than 2 hours. Well worth it.
I love the energy! On a more practical note, the concepts were delivered with exceptional clarity, and the overall structure of the course is excellent.

This short coruse is infact a great content. this course talks about the end to end knowledge a leader should have even he doesn't have the background. Thanks to Ed Donner for sharing the tools kits which are very hand to have for reference aswell as for the tracking the AI initiatives. I finall say that a short but a puching course every leader should go through.
Course is really good. One thing that is not covered well is personal. I would like to see which roles should be filled out first in each case. Which ones are mandatory and which ones are not
It's well structured and easy to follow. A comprehensive roadmap covering all phases and needs for AI projects providing useful tools.
Ed's approach of combining executive-level insights with actionable frameworks seems perfect for professionals at any level looking to understand AI's commercial impact.

It's fun to listen to him and follow his train of thought, even though I come from a technical/AI background. All of his points are valid. I would say that the difficult part now begins: putting this into practice.
The course was excellent! Aligns well with my background and area of focus.
Very comprehensive and highly practical course, enriched with well-crafted frameworks that are practical and actionable for real world scenarios.

As the head of service enablement in our company, I found it very useful in different terms. First of all I am now playing an AI tranformation facilitator role in our company already to conduct a mindset shift in all our colleagues. As part of the leadership in the company, I think we are on the right track but this course definitely generated a very solid roadmap for the next actions that we should take. Thanks!
What an incredible journey this course has been! Donna's 'From AI Strategist to AI Leader' workshop is an absolute gem.

It’s an extremely good lesson for a company working with AI solutions: success requires aligning culture, resources, and change management to effectively execute AI initiatives, build consensus, and achieve the goals and objectives of AI solutions.

Thanks so much, Ed. You are really making a massive difference in the AI/LLM space. I’m so grateful to have taken your three world-class courses. I will definitely leverage the community and network you and your team are creating. Wholehearted thanks!

The Generative AI 2025 Executive Briefing LLMs for Leaders is an excellent fast paced course with a top presenter and industry leader, Ed Donner. This material will help me in my consulting practice to guide my clients to becoming AI success stories. I binged the first pass in a single day and plan to come back and make improvements to my own approaches, presentations, and writings. Thank you, Ed Donner!
This is an extensive briefing to set the foundation of GenAI thinking in right direction from the current hype in the market to the reality.
Excellent briefing and a good follow on to Ed's LLM engineering course. Great blending of AI/LLM specific aspects with solid executive level program management skills.
It would have been helpful if you had few pop quiz modules to check out understanding and memory.
Very high level course mainly for AI Leaders driving strategies. Not intended for developer community.
Wonderful Flow and narration with real life examples that makes it easy for all to understand. Great job Ed !!

This was exactly what I needed! clear, high-level insight for decision makers without the fluff, it was time well spent! I especially appreciated the balance of technical grounding and commercial application. Highly recommend to any executive looking to lead in the AI era!
Fantastic job Ed Donner ! This course is precise , adequately balancing leadership with technicalities, informative and provide with tools to implement. Way to go !

This course is a clear roadmap for implementing AI projects from scratch, something that can often feel overwhelming. It was really engaging and easy to understand. I’d highly recommend it to any leader looking to get a broader understanding of the AI project decision-making process.
An excellent overview course. Covered all the important aspects at the right level.
I am watching this on my cell phone and I find the information easy to follow and very friendly for this format

Yet another fantastic 5-star course from Ed! This time, I learned concrete ways to bring AI into our organization. Ed’s deep expertise and infectious enthusiasm sparked a bunch of ideas for tackling our business pain points with AI. As one of the world’s largest oils and fats companies, we’re still in the infancy of AI adoption—and thanks to this course (and Ed’s excellent LLM and Agents classes), I now fully grasp the urgency of integrating AI across our operations. Thanks again, Ed!

As the course description makes clear, this is aimed at managers and business leaders, not techies—Ed has other courses for the hands-on crowd. I'm more involved in the technical side myself, but I still found some useful concepts here that I can apply in my own startup. This really is an executive briefing: a high-level flyover of key ideas and buzzwords, which at times feels a bit like reading the table of contents of modern AI. But that's the point—it's not meant to teach AI development, it's meant to give decision-makers a broad sense of the landscape. I did get value from it, especially in areas of business and organizational impact that I might otherwise have overlooked. I’d recommend the course, as long as you remember it’s pitched at execs trying to wrap their heads around this whole “AI thing.”

It delivers exactly what the description promises. I love how Ed conveys emotion, you can genuinely feel his passion for the topic. I had just started the Agentic course, but when I saw he released this one today, I jumped in and ended up finishing it in one sitting. As a Product Manager, I truly believe this course should be part of every product learning path

Wow.Ed’s training on AI for leaders was truly refreshing. Unlike the technical or functional sessions, this program focused on what it means to lead in the age of AI & how to think strategically, guide teams, and create vision. It’s not about coding or configurations; it’s about shaping direction. I really appreciated how it bridged the gap between strategy and leadership. A wonderful session that I found both insightful and inspiring.
